The paper focuses on deep neural networks (DNNs) and their deployment on resource-constrained mobile devices, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the challenges of offloading DNNs to the cloud, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). The proposed framework, Edgent, involves collaboration between devices and the edge, which suggests a focus on networking and communication (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of DNN inference, which suggests a focus on optimization and control (cs.NE).
